Pre-revolutionary flags spotted, anthem booed at Iran’s World Cup opener

I don’t think diaspora Iranians in LA who have the kind of cash to attend the most expensive World Cup in history are representative of the general Iranian population. Would be surprised if the US allowed any fans actually based in Iran to attend at all. Awful for the players by the way, treated as less than dirt by the US administration.
I was at the match with my Iranian boyfriend (who is critical of both the current and Shah’s regime). He recognized some attendees near us as having come directly from Iran, which is surprising considering how much they had to go through to get there.;Analytical/Speculative Take;

Dani Ceballos to leave Real Madrid as free agent. Decision made. Ceballos, ready for new chapter as he’s not part of José Mourinho’s plans. Real Betis one of the clubs keen after Ajax tried in May. It’s over between Real and Ceballos.

End of an error. He was highly promising when we signed him from Betis in 2017 but he never kicked on, sad for him.

Feel like he’s been at Madrid since Xbox 360;Drive-By Drop;

